WEBVTT

00:01.033 --> 00:03.033
♪ WHEN THIS BOY MEETS WORLD ♪

00:03.033 --> 00:06.000
♪ BOY MEETS WORLD ♪

00:06.000 --> 00:10.367
♪ WANDERIN' DOWN THIS ROAD
THAT WE CALL LIFE ♪

00:10.367 --> 00:12.667
♪ IS WHAT WE'RE DOIN' ♪

00:12.667 --> 00:14.500
♪ IT'S GOOD TO KNOW
I HAVE FRIENDS ♪

00:14.500 --> 00:16.300
♪ WHO WILL ALWAYS ♪

00:16.300 --> 00:18.734
♪ STAND BY ME ♪

00:18.734 --> 00:21.767
♪ WHEN THIS BOY MEETS WORLD ♪

00:21.767 --> 00:24.467
THIS IS SO FUN --
THE THREE OF US LIVING TOGETHER.

00:24.467 --> 00:26.000
NOTHING BEATS GIRLFRIENDS.

00:26.000 --> 00:27.500
WHAT MOVIES DID YOU RENT?

00:27.500 --> 00:30.200
OH, I HAVE "LITTLE WOMEN,"
"TERMS OF ENDEARMENT,"

00:30.200 --> 00:31.233
AND "EVER AFTER."

00:31.233 --> 00:33.700
I NEVER GOT TO WATCH
THESE KIND OF FILMS

00:33.700 --> 00:35.500
WHEN ERIC AND JACK LIVED HERE.

00:35.500 --> 00:38.734
I'M SO GLAD TO SEE A MOVIE
WITHOUT "BOOTY" IN THE TITLE.

00:38.734 --> 00:40.400
GOOD EVENING, LADIES.

00:40.400 --> 00:42.500
THE BOYFRIENDS
HAVE ARRIVED.

00:42.500 --> 00:43.867
LET THE KISSY-KISSY BEGIN.

00:43.867 --> 00:47.033
HOWDY!
HI!

00:47.033 --> 00:48.700
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

00:48.700 --> 00:50.734
I TOLD YOU WE WERE GONNA HANG
IN THE APARTMENT.

00:50.734 --> 00:53.033
I FIGURE,
YOU AND ANGELA HERE,

00:53.033 --> 00:56.100
ME AND SHAWN NOT HERE --
IT'S JUST NOT RIGHT.

00:56.100 --> 00:57.734
DO THAT THING
I LIKE ON MY EAR.

00:57.734 --> 00:59.000
OH, THAT'S THE ONE!

00:59.000 --> 01:01.200
OH, YEAH! ALL RIGHT.

01:05.767 --> 01:07.500
YES?

01:07.500 --> 01:09.400
WE WERE GONNA WATCH A MOVIE.

01:09.400 --> 01:10.867
Movie?
Dark.

01:10.867 --> 01:12.500
Good. Movie good.

01:12.500 --> 01:15.100
ALL RIGHT.
LET'S SEE WHAT YOU GOT.

01:15.100 --> 01:17.200
"ESTROGEN ON PARADE,"
"PUT DOWN THE SEAT,"

01:17.200 --> 01:19.300
AND "THESE SHOES
OR THESE SHOES."

01:21.800 --> 01:24.500
WELL...THESE ARE ALL
VERY LOVELY.

01:24.500 --> 01:26.400
HOWEVER, NO.

01:26.400 --> 01:29.500
PERHAPS
THE LADIES ARE UNAWARE

01:29.500 --> 01:32.967
OF JENNIFER LOPEZ
vs CARMEN ELECTRA

01:32.967 --> 01:35.700
ON "CELEBRITY DEATHMATCH"...

01:35.700 --> 01:39.033
IN PUDDING...

01:39.033 --> 01:42.400
ON PONIES.

01:42.400 --> 01:44.600
THIS WAS SUPPOSED TO BE
LADIES' NIGHT.

01:44.600 --> 01:46.400
NO, LADIES.
TONIGT IS BOOTY NIGHT.

01:46.400 --> 01:48.000
OH, YEAH.

01:55.400 --> 01:58.767
MR. FEENY, THANKS
FOR THE JOB RECOMMENDATION.

01:58.767 --> 02:00.133
MANAGER OF THE STUDENT UNION'S

02:00.133 --> 02:02.100
GONNA LOOK REAL GOOD
ON MY RéSUMé.

02:02.100 --> 02:04.200
WELL, THIS IS YOUR LAST YEAR
IN COLLEGE, JACK.

02:04.200 --> 02:06.734
I THOUGHT THE WORK EXPERIENCE
WOULD BE GOOD FOR YOU.

02:06.734 --> 02:08.967
YEAH, I KNOW
IT'S KIND OF HARD TO BELIEVE

02:08.967 --> 02:12.100
THIS TIME NEXT YEAR I'LL BE OUT
IN THE COLD, CRUEL WORLD.

02:12.100 --> 02:13.600
THINK YOU'RE READY FOR IT?

02:13.600 --> 02:16.400
YEAH.
YEAH, I THINK I'M READY.

02:16.400 --> 02:19.567
HOWEVER,
HIM, I AM WORRIED ABOUT.

02:19.567 --> 02:21.000
HEY, MELISSA.

02:21.000 --> 02:23.734
CLASSICAL CIVILIZATION COURSE
GOT YOU BLUE, HUH?

02:23.734 --> 02:25.400
YOU KNOW WHAT YOU NEED?
BAM!

02:25.400 --> 02:28.500
A LITTLE MORE WHIP CREAM
MAKES EVERYTHING BETTER, BABY.

02:28.500 --> 02:30.600
OH, AND YOU TWO!

02:30.600 --> 02:33.867
WILL YOU PLEASE JUST STOP
DANCING AROUND EACH OTHER?

02:33.867 --> 02:35.900
YOU COME HERE EVERY SINGLE DAY.

02:35.900 --> 02:37.300
YOU SIT ACROSS FROM EACH OTHER.

02:37.300 --> 02:39.600
YOU STARE AT EACH OTHER,
BUT NOBODY DOES NOTHING.

02:39.600 --> 02:41.734
YOU KNOW SOMETHING?
I'M GONNA DO SOMETHING.

02:41.734 --> 02:44.300
I WANT YOU TO TURN AROUND,
LOOK AT EACH OTHER.

02:44.300 --> 02:46.400
I WANT YOU TO SMILE.

02:46.400 --> 02:48.700
HE'S A GOOD-LOOKING GUY.
SMILE AT HIM.

02:48.700 --> 02:50.900
AW, THAT'S SO CUTE.
I WANT AN INVITE, KIDS.

02:50.900 --> 02:53.767
ALL RIGHT? HERE.

02:53.767 --> 02:56.767
DO SOMETHING WITH THAT.
ALL RIGHT?

02:56.767 --> 02:58.400
I DON'T WANT
TO OVERSTEP MY BOUNDS,

02:58.400 --> 03:01.200
BUT WHY WOULD YOU RECOMMEND
<i>HIM </i>AS MY ASSISTANT MANAGER?

03:01.200 --> 03:03.233
WELL, AS YOU SAID,
IT'S A COLD, CRUEL WORLD.

03:03.233 --> 03:05.500
A LITTLE PREPARATION
IS GOOD FOR EVERYBODY.

03:05.500 --> 03:06.767
RIGHT!

03:06.767 --> 03:09.200
I UNDERSTAND
WHAT YOU'RE SAYING NOW.

03:09.200 --> 03:11.600
YOU WANT <i>HIM </i>TO LEARN FROM <i>ME.  </i>

03:11.600 --> 03:14.567
WELL, I WAS HOPING IT
WOULD BE GOOD FOR BOTH OF YOU.

03:14.567 --> 03:15.567
THAT'S GOOD.

03:15.567 --> 03:16.567
MR. FEENY!

03:16.567 --> 03:18.500
ERIC MATTHEWS, BUSINESSMAN.

03:18.500 --> 03:20.200
WHAT DO YOU THINK, HUH?

03:20.200 --> 03:21.600
VERY IMPRESSIVE.

03:21.600 --> 03:22.800
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

03:22.800 --> 03:25.600
OH, FEENY, THAT IS YOU.
WHEN THE NEW MRS. FEENY

03:25.600 --> 03:28.033
GETS A LOOK AT YOU
IN THAT SWEAT SHIRT,

03:28.033 --> 03:30.867
THEY'RE GONNA HAVE TO
HOSE HER DOWN, MY FRIEND.

03:30.867 --> 03:32.900
COME ON.
IT'S JUST A SWEATSHIRT.

03:32.900 --> 03:35.600
STILL, THAT'S A RATHER
MASCULINE PENGUIN, HUH?

03:35.600 --> 03:39.200
PERHAPS FOR THE RIGHT OCCASION,
MIGHT JUST FIT THE BILL.

03:39.200 --> 03:41.233
THAT'S ONLY $19.99,
PLUS TAX.

03:41.233 --> 03:42.600
WHAT'S THE TAX?

03:42.600 --> 03:44.367
IT'S A PERCENTAGE
OF SOMETHING,

03:44.367 --> 03:45.500
BUT I'M NOT REALLY SURE.

03:45.500 --> 03:47.567
CAN I SEE YOU
FOR A MINUTE?

03:47.567 --> 03:48.500
ABSOLUTELY, BOSS.

03:50.700 --> 03:52.300
YOU KNOW SOMETHING, JACK?

03:52.300 --> 03:53.800
THIS WORKING THING IS GREAT.

03:53.800 --> 03:56.200
I-I THINK I'M REALLY
A PEOPLE PERSON, YOU KNOW?

03:56.200 --> 03:59.367
LISTEN, I DON'T WANT TO BUST UP
ON YOUR "PEOPLE" PARADE,

03:59.367 --> 04:01.767
BUT TAKE THIS
TO THE BANK, DEPOSIT IT.

04:01.767 --> 04:03.600
WHOO, THE BANK!
RIGHT ON.

04:03.600 --> 04:04.967
HEY, YOU KNOW WHAT?

04:04.967 --> 04:07.934
THANK YOU FOR GIVING ME
THIS RESPONSIBILITY.

04:07.934 --> 04:10.500
YOU CAN TOTALLY TRUST ME
WITH THIS.

04:10.500 --> 04:12.500
GIVE ME THE BAG!

04:12.500 --> 04:14.600
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO!

04:14.600 --> 04:16.734
I NEED THAT BANK CRAP
ON MY RESUME.

04:16.734 --> 04:18.700
ALL RIGHT.
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.

04:18.700 --> 04:21.500
JUST TAKE IT TO THE BANK,
DEPOSIT THE MONEY,

04:21.500 --> 04:23.200
AND THEN COME RIGHT BACK.

04:23.200 --> 04:25.133
TELL ME WHAT YOU'RE GONNA DO.

04:25.133 --> 04:27.834
I'M GONNA TAKE THE MONEY
TO THE BANK, DEPOSIT IT,

04:27.834 --> 04:29.100
AND COME RIGHT BACK.

04:29.100 --> 04:30.300
KEEP SAYING IT.

04:30.300 --> 04:32.000
TAKE THE MONEY TO THE BANK,
DEPOSIT IT,

04:32.000 --> 04:33.133
AND COME RIGHT BACK.

04:33.133 --> 04:35.300
TAKE THE MONEY TO THE BANK,
DEPOSIT IT,

04:35.300 --> 04:36.700
AND COME RIGHT BACK.

04:36.700 --> 04:39.934
TAKE MY MOM TO SEE FRANK,
CLEAN MY CLOSET, TAKE A NAP.

04:39.934 --> 04:41.500
WHERE AM I?

04:41.500 --> 04:42.900
OH, YEAH!

04:45.100 --> 04:48.200
[ MONKEY SQUEALS ]

04:48.200 --> 04:51.300
[ Italian accent ] SORRY, ERIC,
I JUST DON'T HAVE ENOUGH.

04:51.300 --> 04:52.767
HUH?

04:52.767 --> 04:56.934
I WAS TALKING TO MY FRIEND
HERE -- LITTLE ERIC.

04:56.934 --> 04:58.667
THE MONKEY'S
GOT THE SAME NAME AS ME!

04:58.667 --> 04:59.934
YOUR NAME ERIC?

04:59.934 --> 05:02.934
I'M THE ASSISTANT MANAGER
OF STUDENT UNION.

05:02.934 --> 05:06.600
I'M HERE
DEPOSITING 1,700 SMACKERINOS.

05:06.600 --> 05:10.133
OH, HEY,
THAT'S A LOT OF MONEY.

05:10.133 --> 05:11.934
THAT'S THE KIND OF MONEY
WE NO HAVE.

05:11.934 --> 05:14.467
WHAT DO YOU NEED THE MONEY FOR,
MR. ORGAN GRINDER?

05:14.467 --> 05:16.934
FOR HIS GIRLFRIEND, ISABELLA.

05:16.934 --> 05:18.400
HE'S GOT
A LITTLE MONKEY BABE?

05:18.400 --> 05:19.967
SHE'S STILL IN MILWAUKEE.

05:19.967 --> 05:22.767
I NO HAVE ENOUGH MONEY
TO SEND FOR HER.

05:22.767 --> 05:25.500
ERIC WON'T DO HIS HAPPY DANCE
WITHOUT HER.

05:25.500 --> 05:28.734
NOBODY WANTS TO PAY
TO SEE A DEPRESSED MONKEY.

05:28.734 --> 05:31.500
HOW MUCH DO YOU NEED
TO BRING ISABELLA HERE?

05:31.500 --> 05:34.967
LET'S SEE...
THERE'S SHIPPING, HANDLING,

05:34.967 --> 05:38.800
LITTLE MONKEY CAGE --
1,700 SMACKERINOS!

05:38.800 --> 05:40.500
THAT IS EXACTLY
HOW MUCH I HAVE!

05:40.500 --> 05:43.467
OH, WHAT A COINCIDENCE.

05:43.467 --> 05:45.000
[ LAUGHS ]

05:45.000 --> 05:46.000
OH.

05:46.000 --> 05:47.600
OH...Y-YOU KNOW WHAT?

05:47.600 --> 05:49.700
I THINK YOU SHOULD TAKE THIS.

05:49.700 --> 05:53.200
I-I CAN'T LET MONEY
STAND IN THE WAY OF MONKEY LOVE.

05:53.200 --> 05:54.500
REALLY?!

05:54.500 --> 05:56.900
OH-OH-OH!
YOU'RE A GOOD PERSON.

05:56.900 --> 05:59.500
NOW LITTLE ERIC
WON'T BE DEPRESSED,

05:59.500 --> 06:01.867
AND WE CAN EARN
A LOT OF MONEY.

06:01.867 --> 06:04.767
WHERE CAN I FIND YOU
TO PAY YOU BACK?

06:04.767 --> 06:06.800
AT THE PENNBROOK UNIVERSITY
STUDENT UNION.

06:06.800 --> 06:08.767
WE CANNOT THANK YOU ENOUGH!

06:08.767 --> 06:11.934
LITTLE ERIC,
SHOW THE MAN YOUR HAPPY DANCE!

06:15.600 --> 06:18.600
THAT'S THE SAME
AS MY HAPPY DANCE!

06:24.000 --> 06:26.834
THIS IS SOME GOOD MEAT HERE,
SHAWN.

06:26.834 --> 06:28.500
YOU KNOW WHAT'S GREAT
ABOUT GIRLS?

06:28.500 --> 06:30.500
NOT YET.

06:30.500 --> 06:32.000
THEY CAN NEVER
FINISH A MEAL IN PUBLIC.

06:32.000 --> 06:33.700
THEY ALWAYS BRING IT HOME
TO THEIR REFRIGERATORS,

06:33.700 --> 06:34.967
LIKE SPIDERS.

06:34.967 --> 06:37.033
SHAWN, HAVE YOU TRIED
THE RIB ROAST YET?

06:37.033 --> 06:38.033
MNH-MNH.

06:38.033 --> 06:40.400
TRADE YOU
FOR THIS TURKEY LEG.

06:40.400 --> 06:43.734
MMM...MMM...MMM!

06:43.734 --> 06:45.400
DELISH!

06:46.867 --> 06:48.200
AAH!

06:48.200 --> 06:49.567
HEY, HEY, HEY!

06:49.567 --> 06:52.767
TO WHAT DO WE OWE
THIS FREE LOOKY?

06:52.767 --> 06:54.200
HOW DID YOU GET IN HERE?

06:54.200 --> 06:55.200
BEHOLD...A KEY.

06:55.200 --> 06:56.600
TOPANGA GAVE IT TO ME.

06:56.600 --> 06:59.033
NOW WE CAN COME AND GO
AS WE PLEASE.

06:59.033 --> 07:02.033
I WISH TOPANGA WOULD HAVE
TOLD ME ABOUT IT FIRST.

07:02.033 --> 07:03.133
[ SIGHS ]

07:03.133 --> 07:04.934
SHE DIDN'T TELL YOU?

07:04.934 --> 07:06.767
THAT'S JUST WRONG.

07:06.767 --> 07:09.767
WELL, NOW I JUST FEEL
UNCOMFORTABLE.

07:09.767 --> 07:11.000
THIS IS VERY AWKWARD.

07:11.000 --> 07:14.400
YOU MUST THINK WE'RE BARBARIANS
OR SOMETHING.

07:14.400 --> 07:15.900
NO, NO, I'M SORRY.

07:15.900 --> 07:20.667
I WAS A LITTLE SURPRISED, SEEING
YOU HERE EATING MY FOOD...

07:20.667 --> 07:22.100
WHICH IS MINE.

07:22.100 --> 07:26.200
BUT I'M NOT GONNA KEEP YOU
FROM YOUR GIRLFRIENDS.

07:26.200 --> 07:27.767
YOU'RE NOT?

07:27.767 --> 07:28.867
NO.

07:28.867 --> 07:30.667
SO, YOU WANT US TO STAY?

07:30.667 --> 07:32.567
YEAH, I GUESS.

07:32.567 --> 07:34.467
THEN WE NEED HORSERADISH!

07:34.467 --> 07:35.500
RED, NOT WHITE.

07:35.500 --> 07:37.100
UGH -- WHITE! UGH!

07:37.100 --> 07:39.567
AND WE'RE GONNA NEED
SOME MACARONI AND CHEESE.

07:39.567 --> 07:42.567
RUGRATS.
NOT DINOSAURS!

07:42.567 --> 07:44.567
WE GOT SOME OTHER STUFF, TOO.

07:44.567 --> 07:46.467
BUT WE HAVE A LIST FOR YOU.

07:46.467 --> 07:48.200
WE PUT IT
IN YOUR UNDERWEAR DRAWER.

07:48.200 --> 07:49.934
YOU WERE
IN MY UNDERWEAR DRAWER?!

07:49.934 --> 07:53.500
HEY, WHO GETS TO SEE
THAT LITTLE PURPLE NUMBER?

07:53.500 --> 07:55.367
YOU KNOW WHO GETS TO SEE IT,
SHAWNIE,

07:55.367 --> 07:56.600
IS THAT BOY IN THE DIARY!

07:56.600 --> 07:59.100
OH, THE PURPLE NUMBER IS HOT!

07:59.100 --> 08:01.033
YOU WENT IN MY DIARY?!

08:01.033 --> 08:03.467
YEAH,
YOU'RE A VERY BAD GIRL.

08:03.467 --> 08:06.600
YOU THINK IF <i>WE </i>SAW YOU
IN THE PURPLE UNDERWEAR,

08:06.600 --> 08:08.133
WE'D SCREAM "OH, MAMA!"?

08:08.133 --> 08:10.400
AAHHH, GET OUT!!

08:10.400 --> 08:12.100
OUT, OUT, OUT!

08:12.100 --> 08:13.100
GIVE ME THIS!

08:13.100 --> 08:14.300
HEY!

08:14.300 --> 08:16.300
YOU CAN'T KICK US OUT.
WE'VE GOT A KEY.

08:16.300 --> 08:18.300
NOT ANYMORE, YOU DON'T.

08:18.300 --> 08:19.500
OUT!

08:26.233 --> 08:28.934
OKAY, WAIT A MINUTE.
WHAT'S GOING ON HERE?

08:28.934 --> 08:31.734
HOW COULD YOU NOT EVEN ASK ME
IF THEY COULD HAVE A KEY?

08:31.734 --> 08:32.934
JUST US THREE GIRLS.

08:32.934 --> 08:34.767
REMEMBER
HOW IT'S SUPPOSED TO BE?

08:34.767 --> 08:38.233
OH, RACHEL,
YOU KNOW WE GOT BACK TOGETHER.

08:38.233 --> 08:42.734
THEY ATE ALL OF MY FOOD!

08:42.734 --> 08:47.400
WE NEEDED CARBOS FOR KISSING.

08:47.400 --> 08:49.667
THEY READ MY DIARY.

08:49.667 --> 08:51.033
OH, RACHEL!

08:51.033 --> 08:53.000
THAT'S JUST NOT TRUE.

08:53.000 --> 08:56.734
BUT IF WE DID,
YOU'RE A <i>BAD </i>GIRL.

08:56.734 --> 08:58.800
THEY WENT
THROUGH MY UNDERWEAR DRAWER.

08:58.800 --> 09:01.000
OH, RACHEL,
THAT'S JUST LUDICROUS.

09:01.000 --> 09:03.233
DID YOU?

09:03.233 --> 09:05.467
HE MADE ME!

09:05.467 --> 09:12.100
MY NAME IS SHAWN,
AND I HAVE A PROBLEM.

09:14.767 --> 09:17.467
RACHEL, LOOK HOW CUTE THEY ARE
WHEN THEY'RE GUILTY.

09:17.467 --> 09:19.367
YOU CANNOT BE MAD
AT THESE GUYS.

09:22.100 --> 09:24.834
APOLOGIZE TO HER.

09:24.834 --> 09:28.600
Both: WE'RE SORRY WE WENT
THROUGH YOUR UNDERWEAR, MISS.

09:28.600 --> 09:29.867
IS THAT OKAY?

09:29.867 --> 09:32.467
NOW CAN THEY HAVE
THEIR KEY BACK?

09:32.467 --> 09:34.000
NO, IT'S NOT OKAY.

09:34.000 --> 09:37.400
I FEEL LIKE I CAN'T BE MYSELF
IN MY OWN APARTMENT.

09:37.400 --> 09:39.033
HEY, THAT'S RIDICULOUS!

09:39.033 --> 09:42.767
YOU CAN GO BACK
TO BEING YOUR <i>BAD </i>SELF.

09:42.767 --> 09:44.400
IT'S CORY AND SHAWN.

09:44.400 --> 09:46.600
CORY AND I
ARE GETTING MARRIED.

09:46.600 --> 09:47.800
WE'RE LIKE FAMILY.

09:47.800 --> 09:50.834
IS THAT THE WAY YOU WANT IT?

09:50.834 --> 09:54.100
LET'S <i>ALL </i>BE LIKE FAMILY.
COME ON.

09:54.100 --> 09:57.000
<i>NOW </i>CAN THEY HAVE
THEIR KEY BACK?

09:59.133 --> 10:00.734
FINE.

10:00.734 --> 10:04.000
WE'LL BE LIKE
ONE BIG HAPPY FAMILY.

10:08.900 --> 10:12.600
DON'T YOU EVER GO
NEAR HER UNDERWEAR DRAWER...

10:12.600 --> 10:14.734
EVER AGAIN!

10:14.734 --> 10:16.200
[ PANTING ]

10:16.200 --> 10:17.200
WHA--

10:17.200 --> 10:19.233
NEVER?

10:19.233 --> 10:21.367
WHA--

10:21.367 --> 10:23.500
JUST ONCE?

10:25.200 --> 10:26.233
HEY!

10:26.233 --> 10:27.767
HOW'D IT GO AT THE BANK?

10:27.767 --> 10:28.767
SO GOOD.

10:28.767 --> 10:30.200
GIVE ME THE DEPOSIT SLIP.

10:30.200 --> 10:31.200
DON'T HAVE ONE.

10:31.200 --> 10:33.200
WHY?

10:33.200 --> 10:34.400
I DIDN'T DEPOSIT
THE MONEY.

10:34.400 --> 10:35.767
WHY?!

10:35.767 --> 10:37.100
I DID SOMETHING BETTER
WITH IT.

10:37.100 --> 10:38.367
WHY?

10:38.367 --> 10:41.033
BECAUSE I GAVE IT TO A MONKEY.

10:41.033 --> 10:43.033
YOU GAVE IT TO A MONKEY.

10:43.033 --> 10:45.100
I DIDN'T ACTUALLY
GIVE IT TO A MONKEY.

10:45.100 --> 10:46.767
I GAVE IT TO THE ORGAN GRINDER

10:46.767 --> 10:49.033
SO HE COULD SEND
FOR THE MONKEY'S GIRLFRIEND.

10:49.033 --> 10:50.567
LITTLE APOLOGY MAYBE?

10:50.567 --> 10:52.767
HOW COULD I EVER THINK
YOU COULD BE TRUSTED?

10:52.767 --> 10:54.100
THE MONEY'S NOT GONE.

10:54.100 --> 10:57.033
THE ORGAN GRINDER --
HE PROMISED HE'D PAY ME BACK.

10:57.033 --> 10:58.300
I DID A GOOD THING!

10:58.300 --> 10:59.667
YOU WERE RIPPED OFF.

10:59.667 --> 11:01.500
HE GAVE ME HIS WORD.

11:01.500 --> 11:02.967
GROW UP.

11:02.967 --> 11:05.400
WHEN ARE YOU GONNA GROW UP?

11:05.400 --> 11:06.734
YOU ARE GRADUATING IN MAY.

11:06.734 --> 11:08.300
NO MORE ME, NO MORE PARENTS,
MR. FEENY

11:08.300 --> 11:09.500
TO CLEAN UP
YOUR LITTLE MESSES!

11:09.500 --> 11:11.233
THIS WORLD
IS GONNA CRUSH YOU!

11:11.233 --> 11:13.967
I FEEL SORRY FOR YOU, MAN...

11:13.967 --> 11:16.767
BUT I'M NOT GONNA LET YOU
DRAG ME DOWN WITH YOU.

11:27.400 --> 11:28.600
HEY!

11:28.600 --> 11:30.200
KEEP THOSE LIPS
WHERE I CAN SEE THEM.

11:30.200 --> 11:31.767
WE'RE TRYING TO RUN
A BUSINESS HERE.

11:31.767 --> 11:32.900
GO DO IT IN YOUR CAR.

11:34.800 --> 11:38.300
HEY, ERIC,
OUR HOT CHOCOLATES READY YET?

11:42.000 --> 11:43.500
$4.

11:43.500 --> 11:45.967
I SEE
THAT'S THE ADVERTISED PRICE,

11:45.967 --> 11:50.100
BUT, UH, YOU HAVEN'T FIGURED IN
THE BROTHERLY DISCOUNT OF FREE.

11:50.100 --> 11:52.400
PAY UP, DEADBEAT!

11:52.400 --> 11:54.700
IT'S A COLD, CRUEL WORLD
OUT THERE.

11:54.700 --> 11:58.233
THERE'S NOT GONNA BE PEOPLE
AROUND TO CLEAN UP YOUR MESSES!

11:58.233 --> 12:01.400
I'M TELLING MOM.

12:03.000 --> 12:06.000
GET TO THE POINT, MR. GRISHAM,
I'M GETTING BORED.

12:06.000 --> 12:08.000
HEY, HEY, HEY, READER GUY!

12:08.000 --> 12:09.400
I'M SORRY.

12:09.400 --> 12:10.667
DOES THIS -- MMM, NO --

12:10.667 --> 12:12.767
DOES THIS
LOOK LIKE A LIBRARY TO YOU?

12:12.767 --> 12:14.200
NO, NO, I --

12:14.200 --> 12:16.500
"I WAS JUST, I WAS JUST."
NO, YOU'RE READING IT.

12:16.500 --> 12:18.033
YOU'RE READING IT,
YOU BUY IT.

12:18.033 --> 12:19.300
$14.04 -- COUGH IT UP.

12:19.300 --> 12:20.934
WELL, I --
COUGH IT UP!

12:20.934 --> 12:22.400
I DON'T HAVE ANY PENNIES.

12:22.400 --> 12:23.900
HEY!
WHAT?

12:23.900 --> 12:26.233
BANK IS CLOSED!

12:26.233 --> 12:28.900
I SUPPOSE I COULD PUT IT
ON A CREDIT CARD.

12:28.900 --> 12:31.100
OH, FINE!

12:31.100 --> 12:32.100
THANK YOU.

12:32.100 --> 12:34.100
WHAT IS THIS?
WHAT IS THIS?

12:34.100 --> 12:36.834
YOU SEE YOUR CARD HERE?

12:36.834 --> 12:38.467
YOU SEE THAT? AH!

12:38.467 --> 12:40.967
IT'S BOGUS.
IT EXPIRED IN 1967!

12:40.967 --> 12:44.100
THAT'S "CARDMEMBER SINCE,"
YOU MORON!

12:44.100 --> 12:46.734
WHAT THE HELL'S
WRONG WITH YOU?

12:46.734 --> 12:48.567
ERIC, WHAT ARE THESE BOXES
DOING HERE?

12:48.567 --> 12:50.300
GET THEM DOWN TO THE STOREROOM.

12:50.300 --> 12:52.734
YOU GOT IT, BOSS.
RIGHT AWAY, RIGHT AWAY.

12:52.734 --> 12:55.300
WATCH OUT
FOR THAT GUY OVER THERE.

12:57.100 --> 12:58.133
WHAT DID YOU DO TO HIM?

12:58.133 --> 13:00.834
OH, I TOLD HIM TO BE
MORE RESPONSIBLE.

13:00.834 --> 13:03.400
I KNOW WHEN YOU PUT HIM
TOGETHER WITH ME,

13:03.400 --> 13:06.000
YOU WANTED A LITTLE BIT OF ME
TO RUB OFF ON HIM.

13:06.000 --> 13:07.834
WELL, IT DID.

13:07.834 --> 13:10.567
HE'S EFFICIENT
FOR THE FIRST TIME IN HIS LIFE.

13:10.567 --> 13:12.200
HE'S BETTER OFF FOR IT, TOO.

13:12.200 --> 13:14.700
THIS WHOLE STUDENT UNION
IS BETTER OFF FOR IT,

13:14.700 --> 13:17.900
DON'T YOU THINK?

13:20.300 --> 13:25.300
FRANKLY, MR. HUNTER,
THIS PLACE GIVES ME THE WILLIES.

13:32.567 --> 13:36.300
[ Monotone ] MAY I HELP
THE NEXT PERSON IN LINE?

13:36.300 --> 13:38.967
[ Monotone ] MAY I HELP
THE NEXT PERSON IN LINE?

13:38.967 --> 13:42.667
TAKE THIS WEEK'S RECEIPTS,
GO TO THE BANK, DEPOSIT THEM.

13:42.667 --> 13:44.767
HOW HARD CAN THAT POSSIBLY BE?

13:44.767 --> 13:47.700
PLEASE...
I'M ONLY TWO PAYMENTS BEHIND.

13:47.700 --> 13:49.700
I'M SORRY.
THERE'S NOTHING I CAN DO.

13:49.700 --> 13:52.400
BUT IF YOU TAKE MY CAR,
I CAN'T GET TO WORK.

13:52.400 --> 13:54.133
I CAN'T MAKE ANY PAYMENTS.

13:54.133 --> 13:57.900
I'M THE SOLE SUPPORT
OF MY KIDS.

13:57.900 --> 13:59.300
HOW DO I DRIVE THEM TO SCHOOL?

14:01.400 --> 14:02.800
ALL RIGHT.

14:02.800 --> 14:05.834
I WON'T REPORT THIS JUST YET
IF YOU GIVE ME YOUR WORD

14:05.834 --> 14:09.000
THAT YOU CAN MAKE PAYMENT
ON TIME THIS MONTH.

14:09.000 --> 14:10.467
HER WORD?

14:12.200 --> 14:13.834
MIGHT I EXPLAIN TO YOU

14:13.834 --> 14:16.734
WHAT THE INHERENT VALUE
OF HER WORD IS?

14:18.200 --> 14:21.767
ZILCH, ZIPPO, GOOSE EGG.

14:21.767 --> 14:23.600
WHY ARE YOU SO MEAN?

14:23.600 --> 14:27.400
BECAUSE, MADAM,
THIS IS CORPORATE AMERICA,

14:27.400 --> 14:28.867
NOT CANDY LAND.

14:28.867 --> 14:30.500
AND AS FOR YOU...

14:33.100 --> 14:37.567
YOU WERE GOING TO GIVE THIS
WOMAN SOME SORT OF...CHARITY,

14:37.567 --> 14:38.600
WEREN'T YOU?

14:39.834 --> 14:41.100
YES.

14:41.100 --> 14:43.734
I'M TIRED
OF CLEANING UP YOUR MESSES!

14:43.734 --> 14:45.500
YOU KNOW WHAT YOU'RE GOING
TO AMOUNT TO IN THIS WORLD?

14:45.500 --> 14:48.200
ZILCH, ZIPPO, GOOSE EGG!

14:48.200 --> 14:50.100
I'M SORRY.
I'LL CHANGE.

14:50.100 --> 14:51.867
I'LL BE MORE LIKE YOU.

14:51.867 --> 14:53.734
NO.

14:53.734 --> 14:56.033
DON'T -- DON'T BE LIKE ME.

14:56.033 --> 14:58.400
DON'T BE LIKE ME AT ALL.

14:58.400 --> 15:00.500
I'M SORRY. EXCUSE ME.

15:00.500 --> 15:01.600
MA'AM...
[ SIGHS ]

15:01.600 --> 15:05.567
YOU TAKE THIS.
YOU NEED IT.

15:05.567 --> 15:09.200
YOU MAKE YOUR PAYMENT
AND DRIVE YOUR KIDS TO SCHOOL.

15:09.200 --> 15:12.734
WELL, I-I DON'T KNOW
HOW TO THANK YOU.

15:12.734 --> 15:16.300
I-I-I'LL PAY YOU BACK
AS SOON AS I CAN.

15:16.300 --> 15:18.700
NO, DON'T WORRY ABOUT THAT.

15:18.700 --> 15:20.600
THAT'S NOT IMPORTANT.

15:20.600 --> 15:22.033
THAT'S NOT IMPORTANT.

15:22.033 --> 15:26.367
THIS IS ALL YOUR FAULT,
FENSWEGLER.

15:28.900 --> 15:30.200
ARE YOU SURE
WE SHOULD BE DOING THIS?

15:30.200 --> 15:31.767
YEAH, I FEEL KIND OF BAD.

15:31.767 --> 15:33.734
RACHEL'S ALONE
IN THE OTHER ROOM.

15:33.734 --> 15:36.500
SHE WAS REAL TICKED OFF
ABOUT THE DIARY AND STUFF.

15:36.500 --> 15:37.967
YOU GUYS APOLOGIZED.

15:37.967 --> 15:41.200
SHE UNDERSTANDS THAT YOU GUYS
HAVE EVERY RIGHT TO BE HERE.

15:41.200 --> 15:44.000
YEAH, YOU HEARD HER --
"WE'RE ONE BIG HAPPY FAMILY."

15:44.000 --> 15:45.367
WELL, IN THAT CASE...

15:45.367 --> 15:47.867
WE GOT A LOT MORE KISSING
TO DO.

15:47.867 --> 15:51.300
HEY, GUYS.

15:51.300 --> 15:52.400
HEY, WE WERE JUST...

15:52.400 --> 15:54.600
FI-I-I-I-NE.
HE-E-E-E-Y.

15:54.600 --> 15:56.734
OH, DON'T STOP ON MY ACCOUNT.

15:56.734 --> 15:59.500
REMEMBER --
WE'RE ONE BIG HAPPY FAMILY.

16:00.934 --> 16:02.867
YOU DON'T MIND
IF I PLAY SOME MUSIC, DO YOU?

16:11.834 --> 16:12.834
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?!

16:12.834 --> 16:14.834
DISHES!

16:14.834 --> 16:16.133
DON'T STOP.

16:16.133 --> 16:17.834
DO THE DISHES.

16:17.834 --> 16:19.834
SCRUB-A-DUB-DUB!

16:19.834 --> 16:22.600
OH, DON'T YOU LOVE THIS MUSIC?

16:22.600 --> 16:23.934
I DO NOW.

16:26.100 --> 16:28.200
ISN'T THAT
A LITTLE COLD?

16:28.200 --> 16:29.300
NO!

16:29.300 --> 16:32.400
NO!
SHE'S NOT COLD.

16:32.400 --> 16:34.000
YOU GUYS HAVE A LITTLE ROOM
FOR ME ON THE COUCH?

16:34.000 --> 16:35.100
YES!
CERTAINLY!

16:35.100 --> 16:36.100
OW!

16:36.100 --> 16:37.100
CORY!

16:37.100 --> 16:38.200
SHAWN!

16:38.200 --> 16:39.300
SORRY.
SORRY.

16:39.300 --> 16:41.100
STOP LOOKING AT HER!

16:41.100 --> 16:42.200
SHAWN!

16:42.200 --> 16:44.600
OH, HOW CAN YOU BE MAD
AT THESE TWO?

16:44.600 --> 16:45.834
THEY ARE SO CUTE!

16:45.834 --> 16:47.000
NO, THEY ARE NOT CUTE!

16:47.000 --> 16:48.600
THEY ARE PIGS!

16:48.600 --> 16:50.767
BUT IT'S CUTE
WHEN THEY LOOK AT MY UNDERWEAR

16:50.767 --> 16:52.400
AS LONG AS I'M NOT WEARING IT?

16:52.400 --> 16:53.900
NO, BUT --

16:53.900 --> 16:55.100
WHAT ABOUT MY DIARY?

16:55.100 --> 16:56.100
WHAT WE WERE SAYING --

16:56.100 --> 16:57.667
WAIT.
I HAVE A QUESTION.

16:57.667 --> 17:02.200
ARE YOU GONNA DO THE DISHES
SOME MORE?

17:02.200 --> 17:03.867
OKAY, OKAY.

17:03.867 --> 17:05.000
WE'RE LEAVING.

17:05.000 --> 17:06.000
WE ARE?

17:06.000 --> 17:07.200
YES, CORY.

17:07.200 --> 17:09.100
GIVE ME YOUR KEY.

17:09.100 --> 17:10.934
NO!

17:12.567 --> 17:14.133
WHAT JUST HAPPENED?

17:14.133 --> 17:16.967
WE'RE NOT PART
OF THE FAMILY ANYMORE.

17:20.200 --> 17:22.400
THEY'RE NOT CUTE.
THEY'RE PIGS.

17:22.400 --> 17:23.667
AND WE WERE INSENSITIVE.

17:23.667 --> 17:25.800
WE SHOULD HAVE CONSIDERED
YOUR PRIVACY.

17:25.800 --> 17:27.400
NO. I LOVE THE GUYS.

17:27.400 --> 17:29.300
THEY OBVIOUSLY
LOVE YOU, TOO.

17:29.300 --> 17:31.100
I JUST DON'T WANT TO BE
TAKEN ADVANTAGE OF.

17:31.100 --> 17:32.934
I THINK WE SHOULD SET
SOME BOUNDARIES.

17:32.934 --> 17:34.934
WELL, <i>WE'VE </i>LEARNED
OUR LESSON.

17:34.934 --> 17:36.467
THE GUYS HAVE, TOO.

17:36.467 --> 17:39.000
I'M SURE THEY'RE THINKING
ABOUT IT THE WHOLE WAY HOME.

17:39.000 --> 17:41.300
COME ON, TOPANGA!
MOVE OUT OF THE WAY.

17:41.300 --> 17:42.400
I WANT TO SEE THE UNDERWEAR.

17:42.400 --> 17:43.800
CORY, LET ME LOOK!

17:43.800 --> 17:45.467
I HAVEN'T SEEN ANYTHING YET.

17:45.467 --> 17:47.000
YOU'RE ALMOST MARRIED!

17:47.000 --> 17:48.400
ALMOST!

17:48.400 --> 17:50.467
YOU KNOW WHAT?
WE'RE BIG PIGS.

17:50.467 --> 17:52.033
T-THIS IS WRONG.

17:55.000 --> 17:56.500
HEY, HEY, HEY!

17:56.500 --> 17:59.734
SAME STIRRER...
SAME STIRRER...

17:59.734 --> 18:01.200
SAME STIRRER!

18:01.200 --> 18:02.800
ERIC, IT'S OKAY.

18:02.800 --> 18:04.233
YOU KNOW SOMETHING, JACK?

18:04.233 --> 18:06.500
IT'S <i>NOT </i>OKAY.

18:06.500 --> 18:08.934
SHARE THE SWEET 'N LOW.
SHARE IT.

18:08.934 --> 18:10.467
SWEET...

18:10.467 --> 18:11.800
LOW.

18:11.800 --> 18:14.400
NO, ERIC, LISTEN.

18:14.400 --> 18:16.200
I DON'T WANT YOU TO CHANGE.

18:16.200 --> 18:18.934
COME BACK, MAN.
WHERE'S MY OLD BUDDY?

18:18.934 --> 18:20.000
HE'S DEAD. HE'S GONE.

18:20.000 --> 18:21.300
HE WAS INEFFICIENT

18:21.300 --> 18:23.667
AND UNPREPARED
FOR THAT COLD, CRUEL WORLD.

18:23.667 --> 18:26.133
YOU DID HIM A FAVOR,
AND YOU KILLED HIM.

18:26.133 --> 18:28.667
SAME STIRRER!
HOW HARD IS THAT?

18:28.667 --> 18:31.300
THIS WORLD
IS ONLY COLD AND CRUEL

18:31.300 --> 18:33.867
BECAUSE PEOPLE LIKE ME
BELIEVE

18:33.867 --> 18:35.600
YOU HAVE TO BE THAT WAY
TO SUCCEED.

18:35.600 --> 18:36.867
YOU KNOW SOMETHING, JACK?

18:36.867 --> 18:38.000
I'M GONNA SUCCEED IN IT.

18:38.000 --> 18:39.734
ONE NAPKIN!

18:39.734 --> 18:41.600
LOOK, ERIC, PLEASE, MAN.

18:41.600 --> 18:42.967
I WAS WRONG.

18:42.967 --> 18:44.367
JUST FORGET ALL THAT.

18:44.367 --> 18:47.033
WE DON'T WANT TO BE
ANY PART OF THAT WORLD.

18:47.033 --> 18:48.900
[ SIGHS ]

18:55.100 --> 18:57.900
YOU KNEW THAT, DIDN'T YOU?

18:57.900 --> 19:00.500
WELL, I'VE LIVED IN THIS WORLD
A LONG TIME NOW.

19:00.500 --> 19:02.300
I THINK I KNOW IT
FAIRLY WELL.

19:02.300 --> 19:06.000
SO ALL THIS TIME, YOU DIDN'T
WANT ME TO RUB OFF ON HIM.

19:06.000 --> 19:08.567
YOU WANTED HIM
TO RUB OFF ON ME.

19:08.567 --> 19:10.000
I WANTED BOTH, JACK.

19:10.000 --> 19:12.600
YOU SEE,
IT'S NOT ENOUGH TO LEAVE SCHOOL

19:12.600 --> 19:15.967
AND JUST DESIRE TO SUCCEED
IN THIS COLD, CRUEL WORLD,

19:15.967 --> 19:18.934
BECAUSE THEN YOU SIMPLY BECOME
A PART OF IT.

19:18.934 --> 19:23.367
YOU MUST ALSO HAVE
THE DESIRE TO CHANGE IT.

19:23.367 --> 19:25.100
AND TO CHANGE IT,

19:25.100 --> 19:29.400
YOU NEED YOUR FINE MIND
AND HIS GOOD HEART.

19:29.400 --> 19:31.367
YEAH, MR. FEENY,
YOU SAVED THE DAY.

19:31.367 --> 19:33.500
LOOK, JACK, I'M GONNA NEED
THE DAY'S RECEIPTS.

19:33.500 --> 19:35.400
I'LL PUT THEM
IN THE CASH REGISTER.

19:35.400 --> 19:37.200
DON'T HAVE THEM.

19:37.200 --> 19:38.867
WHY NOT?

19:38.867 --> 19:42.600
BECAUSE I GAVE THE MONEY
TO SOMEONE WHO REALLY NEEDED IT.

19:42.600 --> 19:45.100
PLEASE TELL ME YOU DID NOT FALL
FOR SOMEBODY'S SOB STORY.

19:45.100 --> 19:46.600
YEAH, ACTUALLY, I DID.

19:46.600 --> 19:50.000
I'M GONNA BE WORKING DAY
AND NIGHT HERE TO PAY THAT BACK.

19:50.000 --> 19:51.100
BUT IT'S OKAY.

19:51.100 --> 19:53.734
SOMEHOW I FINALLY
FOUND MY PRIORITIES.

19:53.734 --> 19:54.967
YOU KNOW SOMETHING, JACK?

19:54.967 --> 19:56.300
YOU'RE NEVER GONNA SEE
THAT MONEY AGAIN.

19:56.300 --> 19:58.600
YOU ARE AS STUPID
AS I USED TO BE.

20:01.367 --> 20:03.000
[ SQUEALING ]

20:04.834 --> 20:07.500
HEY, IT'S LITTLE ERIC
AND BIG ERIC!

20:07.500 --> 20:09.033
LITTLE ERIC, IS THAT YOU?

20:09.033 --> 20:12.000
I GOT ONE MORE SURPRISE
FOR EVERYBODY.

20:12.000 --> 20:14.400
[ Singsong voice ]
ISABELLA!

20:14.400 --> 20:16.934
[ SQUEALING ]

20:16.934 --> 20:19.800
HERE'S THAT NICE MAN
I TOLD YOU ABOUT.

20:19.800 --> 20:21.934
IT'S -- IT'S YOU!
YOU CAME BACK.

20:21.934 --> 20:24.800
I KNEW HE'D COME BACK.
DIDN'T I SAY THAT, JACK?

20:24.800 --> 20:26.800
YOU DID GOOD, MAN.

20:26.800 --> 20:29.200
OF COURSE I CAME BACK.
I GAVE YOU MY WORD.

20:29.200 --> 20:31.033
AND HERE'S THE MONEY
I BORROWED.

20:31.033 --> 20:34.867
OH, YOU MADE TWO MONKEYS
VERY HAPPY.

20:34.867 --> 20:37.100
OH, YOU'RE A GOOD BOY.

20:37.100 --> 20:38.967
DON'T EVER CHANGE!

20:40.700 --> 20:43.200
YOU'RE A GOOD BOY.
DON'T EVER CHANGE.

20:43.200 --> 20:45.200
I'LL TRY NOT TO.

20:45.200 --> 20:47.500
OKAY?
